<subSubSection id="679A654DFF880168ECB36FDAE56700DC" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="description">
<paragraph id="2F3F36C6FF880168ECB36FDAE2B40008" blockId="28.[136,1452,1418,2093]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FF880168ECB36FDAE73A029C" bold="true" box="[189,327,1418,1444]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Description</emphasis>
:—Herbs, annual, with taproot. Stems usually prostrate, occasionally ascending, often mat-forming, 
<quantity id="E8789B23FF880168EC866FFEE69202F1" box="[136,239,1454,1481]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="cm" value="25.0" valueMax="45.0" valueMin="5.0">5–45 cm</quantity>
, sericeous or villous. Leaves opposite; stipules distinct, linear-subulate, sometimes irregularly 2–3-lobed, 1.0– 
<quantity id="E8789B23FF880168ECB56F82E76F02D5" box="[187,274,1490,1517]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
, sparsely short-sericeous to sericeous or villous; petiole 
<quantity id="E8789B23FF880168EF9E6F82E26702D5" box="[912,1050,1490,1517]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="1.0" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="0.5">0.5–1.5 mm</quantity>
, sericeous to villous; blade oblongovate to elliptic, 4–18 × 2.5–8.0 mm, base strongly asymmetric, margins serrulate or subentire, apex rounded or broadly acute, abaxial surface pale greyish green, villous, adaxial surface usually with reddish spot, glabrate or with sparse hairs; palmately veined at base, pinnate distally. Cyathia solitary or in small, cymose clusters at distal nodes or on congested, axillary branches; peduncle 
<quantity id="E8789B23FF880168EE646C32E4880145" box="[618,757,1634,1661]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="0.35" valueMax="0.6" valueMin="0.1">0.1–0.6 mm</quantity>
. Involucre obconic, 0.8–1 × 
<quantity id="E8789B23FF880168E8356C32E2BB0145" box="[1083,1222,1634,1661]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="0.7" valueMax="0.8" valueMin="0.6">0.6–0.8 mm</quantity>
, sparsely strigose to sericeous; glands 4, green to yellow-green or pinkish, narrowly oblong, 0.1–0.2 × 
<quantity id="E8789B23FF880168E8236CD6E2C50199" box="[1069,1208,1670,1697]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="0.35" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.5 mm</quantity>
; appendages white to reddish, lunate to oblong, 0.1–0.3 × 
<quantity id="E8789B23FF880168EE266CFAE4CE01FD" box="[552,691,1706,1733]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="15.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="0.85" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="0.2">0.2–1.5 mm</quantity>
, margin crenulate. Staminate flowers 2–5. Pistillate flowers: ovary sericeous; styles 
<quantity id="E8789B23FF880168ED496C9EE7AD01D1" box="[327,464,1742,1769]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="0.35" valueMax="0.4" valueMin="0.3">0.3–0.4 mm</quantity>
, 2-fid at apex. Capsules ovoid, well exserted from involucre at maturity, 1.3–1.5 × 
<quantity id="E8789B23FF880168E9746C9EE69C0035" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2999999999999998" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="1.2999999999999998" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.2">1.2– 1.4 mm</quantity>
, moderately and evenly sericeous; columella 1.0– 
<quantity id="E8789B23FF880168EF1D6CA2E5110035" box="[787,876,1778,1805]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
. Seeds white to light brown, oblong-ovoid, sharply angular in cross section, 1.0–1.2 × 
<quantity id="E8789B23FF880168EE016D46E4E50009" box="[527,664,1814,1841]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="0.75" valueMax="0.9" valueMin="0.6">0.6–0.9 mm</quantity>
, with 3–4 low, transverse ridges that cross angles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2F3F36C6FF880168ECB36D6AE7E400A4" blockId="28.[136,1452,1418,2093]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FF880168ECB36D6AE728006C" bold="true" box="[189,341,1850,1876]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Iconography</emphasis>
:— 
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FF880168ED796D6AE4D5006C" author="Pignatti, S. &amp; Guarino, R. &amp; La Rosa, M." box="[375,680,1850,1876]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref32637" refString="Pignatti, S., Guarino, R. &amp; La Rosa, M. (2017) Flora d'italia, Ed. 2, 4. Edagricole, Bologna, 1178 pp." type="book" year="2017">
Pignatti 
