(2017: 324)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FF880168EEB86D6AE26E006C" author="Pahlevani, A. H. &amp; Riina, R." box="[694,1043,1850,1876]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="304 - 316" refId="ref32314" refString="Pahlevani, A. H. &amp; Riina, R. (2011) A synopsis of Euphorbia subgen. Chamaesyce (Euphorbiaceae) in Iran. Annales Botanici Fennici 48: 304 - 316. https: // doi. org / 10.5735 / 085.048.0402" type="journal article" year="2011">Pahlevani &amp; Riina (2011: 312</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="B7BB2A43FF880168E82F6D6AE21B006D" box="[1057,1126,1850,1877]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[136,229,1872,1894]" captionTargetBox="[251,1334,285,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-63@10.[250,1335,284,1848]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Euphorbia berteroana:A) exsiccatum from Guadaloupe preserved at TO, B) detail of terminal glomerule with short peduncle (scale = 0.5 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5422313" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5422313/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), 
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FF880168E8716D6AE33C006C" author="Jercinovic, E." box="[1151,1345,1850,1876]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 14" refId="ref30744" refString="Jercinovic, E. (2007) The status of the genus Chamaesyce in New Mexico. The New Mexico Botanist 40: 1 - 14." type="journal article" year="2007">Jercinovic (2007</bibRefCitation>
