), 
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FF880168E92A6D0EE6C900A4" author="Hegi, G." pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref30094" refString="Hegi, G. (1924) Illustrierte Flora von Mittel-Europa 5 (1). Verlag von J. F. Lehmann, Munchen, 674 pp." type="book" year="1924">Hegi (1924: 146</bibRefCitation>
, Fig. 1757), Fig. 19.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2F3F36C6FF880168ECB36DF6E56700DC" blockId="28.[136,1452,1418,2093]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FF880168ECB36DF6E7B900F8" bold="true" box="[189,452,1958,1984]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Chromosome number</emphasis>
:—2n = 28 (
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FF880168EE406DF6E53100F9" author="Steinmann, V. W. &amp; Morawetz, J. J. &amp; Berry, P. E. &amp; Peirson, J. A. &amp; Yang, Y." box="[590,844,1958,1985]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="251 - 293" refId="ref34413" refString="Steinmann, V. W., Morawetz, J. J., Berry, P. E., Peirson, J. A. &amp; Yang, Y. (2016) Euphorbia Linnaeus sect. Anisophyllum Roeper. In: Rabeler, R. K. &amp; Hartman, R. L. (Eds.) Flora of North America 12. Oxford University Press, New York, Oxford, pp. 251 - 293." type="book chapter" year="2016">
Steinmann 
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FF880168EEC16DF7E57500F8" box="[719,776,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
); 2n = 12, 40 (
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FF880168EFFF6DF6E2BE00F8" author="Chung, G. Y. &amp; Oh, B. U. &amp; Park, K. R. &amp; Kim, J. H. &amp; Kim, M. S. &amp; Nam, G. H. &amp; Jang, C. G." box="[1009,1219,1958,1984]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="279 - 293" refId="ref27806" refString="Chung, G. Y., Oh, B. U., Park, K. R., Kim, J. H., Kim, M. S., Nam, G. H. &amp; Jang, C. G. (2003) Cytotaxonomic study of Korean Euphorbia L. (Euphorbiaceae). Korean Journal of Plant Taxonomy, 33 (3): 279 - 293. https: // doi. org / 10.11110 / kjpt. 2003.33.3.279" type="journal article" year="2003">
Chung 
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FF880168E84B6DF7E20300F8" box="[1093,1150,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
2003
</bibRefCitation>
); 2n = 42 (
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FF880168E9336DF6E76C00DC" author="Benedi, C. &amp; Orell, J. J." pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="9 - 55" refId="ref26618" refString="Benedi, C. &amp; Orell, J. J. (1992 a) Taxonomy of the genus Chamaesyce SF Gray (Euphorbiaceae) in the Iberian Peninsula and the Balearic Islands. Collectanea botanica 21: 9 - 55. https: // doi. org / 10.3989 / collectbot. 1992. v 21.92" type="journal article" year="1992">Benedì &amp; Orell 1992a</bibRefCitation>
); n = 7 (
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FF880168ED636D9AE79300DC" author="Ward, D. E." box="[365,494,1994,2020]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="302 - 309" refId="ref35468" refString="Ward, D. E. (1983) Chromosome counts from New Mexico and southern Colorado. Phytologia 54: 302 - 309. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 14424" type="journal article" year="1983">Ward 1983</bibRefCitation>
); n = 12, 28 (
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FF880168EE8D6D9AE57000DC" author="Subils, R." box="[643,781,1994,2020]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="83 - 248" refId="ref34581" refString="Subils, R. (1977) Las especies de Euphorbia de la Republica Argentina. Kurtziana 10: 83 - 248." type="journal article" year="1977">Subils 1977</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="679A654DFF880169ECB36DBEE231057D" lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="30" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="2F3F36C6FF880169ECB36DBEE6AC07E5" blockId="28.[136,1452,1418,2093]" lastBlockId="29.[136,1452,158,725]" lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="30" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FF880168ECB36DBEE7610F30" bold="true" box="[189,284,2030,2056]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Ecology</emphasis>
:—Accidentally dispersed by humans, other animals and vehicles as contaminant; globally considered as weed of cereals, cotton, orchards, plantations, vegetables and pastures as well as of human settlements. This species is a common weed of disturbed areas, botanical gardens, sidewalk cracks, railroads and roadsides (
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FF890169E8E16ACEE6B807E5" author="Steinmann, V. W. &amp; Morawetz, J. J. &amp; Berry, P. E. &amp; Peirson, J. A. &amp; Yang, Y." pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="251 - 293" refId="ref34413" refString="Steinmann, V. W., Morawetz, J. J., Berry, P. E., Peirson, J. A. &amp; Yang, Y. (2016) Euphorbia Linnaeus sect. Anisophyllum Roeper. In: Rabeler, R. K. &amp; Hartman, R. L. (Eds.) Flora of North America 12. Oxford University Press, New York, Oxford, pp. 251 - 293." type="book chapter" year="2016">
Steinmann 
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FF890169E97C6ACFE3D10780" box="[1394,1452,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2F3F36C6FF890169ECB36AB6E4C50654" blockId="29.[136,1452,158,725]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FF890169ECB36AB6E7370638" bold="true" box="[189,330,230,256]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Alien status</emphasis>
:—Neophyte native to North and central America, it can be considered invasive in 
<collectingCountry id="57977656FF890169E8EB6AB6E3670638" box="[1253,1306,230,256]" name="Italy" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Italy</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName id="E8804D45FF890169E92A6AB7E3D60638" box="[1316,1451,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Chamaesyce" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FF890169E92A6AB7E3D60638" box="[1316,1451,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">E. maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a globally widespread species naturalized in most of European countries. In Europe, first records are for 
<collectingCountry id="57977656FF890169E94D6B5BE3F2061D" box="[1347,1423,267,293]" name="France" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">France</collectingCountry>
at the end of XVIII century, probably introduced from Africa as seed contaminant (
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FF890169E81C6B7EE2C10670" author="Thellung, A." box="[1042,1212,302,328]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="741 - 772" refId="ref34703" refString="Thellung, A. (1907) Die in Europa bis jetzt beobachteten Euphorbia - Arten der Sektion Anisophyllum. Bulletin de L'Herbier Boissier, ser. 2 7: 741 - 772." type="journal article" year="1907">Thellung 1907</bibRefCitation>
). First Italian records are from LOM and TOS in 1876 (
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FF890169EE0C6B02E4D60654" author="Thellung, A." box="[514,683,338,364]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="741 - 772" refId="ref34703" refString="Thellung, A. (1907) Die in Europa bis jetzt beobachteten Euphorbia - Arten der Sektion Anisophyllum. Bulletin de L'Herbier Boissier, ser. 2 7: 741 - 772." type="journal article" year="1907">Thellung 1907</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2F3F36C6FF890169ECB36B26E57B068C" blockId="29.[136,1452,158,725]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FF890169ECB36B26E7D506A8" bold="true" box="[189,424,374,400]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Occurrence in 
<collectingCountry id="57977656FF890169ED7E6B26E7D506A8" box="[368,424,374,400]" name="Italy" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Italy</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
:—All Italian regions: invasive in PIE, LOM, VEN, TOS, MAR, LAZ, ABR, MOL, CAM, PUG; naturalized in other regions (
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FF890169EE1F6BCAE487068C" author="Galasso, G. &amp; Conti, F. &amp; Peruzzi, L. &amp; Ardenghi, N. M. G. &amp; Banfi, E. &amp; Celesti-Grapow, L. &amp; Albano, A. &amp; Alessandrini, A. &amp; Bacchetta, G. &amp; Ballelli, S. &amp; Bandini Mazzanti, M. &amp; Barberis, G. &amp; Bernardo, L. &amp; Blasi, C. &amp; Bouvet, D. &amp; Bovio, M. &amp; Cecchi, L. &amp; Del Guacchio, E. &amp; Domina, G. &amp; Fascetti, S. &amp; Gallo, L. &amp; Gubellini, L. &amp; Guiggi, A. &amp; Iamonico, D. &amp; Iberite, M. &amp; Jimenez-Mejias, P. &amp; Lattanzi, E. &amp; Marchetti, D. &amp; Martinetto, E. &amp; Masin, R. R. &amp; Medagli, P. &amp; Passalacqua, N. G. &amp; Peccenini, S. &amp; Pennesi, R. &amp; Pierini, B. &amp; Podda, L. &amp; Poldini, L. &amp; Prosser, F. &amp; Raimondo, F. M. &amp; Roma-Marzio, F. &amp; Rosati, L. &amp; Santangelo, A. &amp; Scoppola, A. &amp; Scortegagna, S. &amp; Selvaggi, A. &amp; Selvi, F. &amp; Soldano, A. &amp; Stinca, A. &amp; Wagensommer, R. P. &amp; Wilhalm, T. &amp; Bartolucci, F." box="[529,762,410,436]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="556 - 592" refId="ref28528" refString="Galasso, G., Conti, F., Peruzzi, L., Ardenghi, N. M. G., Banfi, E., Celesti-Grapow, L., Albano, A., Alessandrini, A., Bacchetta, G., Ballelli, S., Bandini Mazzanti, M., Barberis, G., Bernardo, L., Blasi, C., Bouvet, D., Bovio, M., Cecchi, L., Del Guacchio, E., Domina, G., Fascetti, S., Gallo, L., Gubellini, L., Guiggi, A., Iamonico, D., Iberite, M., Jimenez-Mejias, P., Lattanzi, E., Marchetti, D., Martinetto, E., Masin, R. R., Medagli, P., Passalacqua, N. G., Peccenini, S., Pennesi, R., Pierini, B., Podda, L., Poldini, L., Prosser, F., Raimondo, F. M., Roma-Marzio, F., Rosati, L., Santangelo, A., Scoppola, A., Scortegagna, S., Selvaggi, A., Selvi, F., Soldano, A., Stinca, A., Wagensommer, R. P., Wilhalm, T. &amp; Bartolucci, F. (2018 a) An updated checklist of the vascular flora alien to Italy. Plant Biosystems 152: 556 - 592. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 11263504.2018.1441197" type="journal article" year="2018">
Galasso 
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FF890169EE7C6BCBE4D7068C" box="[626,682,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">et al.</emphasis>
2018a
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2F3F36C6FF890169ECB36BEEE231057D" blockId="29.[136,1452,158,725]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FF890169ECB36BEEE7A506E0" bold="true" box="[189,472,446,472]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Taxonomic annotations</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="E8804D45FF890169EDF26BEEE49A06E0" box="[508,743,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FF890169EDF26BEEE49A06E0" box="[508,743,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Euphorbia maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is often confused with 
<taxonomicName id="E8804D45FF890169E80C6BEFE2E206E0" box="[1026,1183,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humistrata">
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FF890169E80C6BEFE2E206E0" box="[1026,1183,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">E. humistrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E8804D45FF890169E8D06BEFE30E06E0" box="[1246,1395,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="thymifolia">
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FF890169E8D06BEFE30E06E0" box="[1246,1395,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">E. thymifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see taxonomic annotations of 
<taxonomicName id="E8804D45FF890169EDA46BB3E43C06C4" box="[426,577,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humistrata">
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FF890169EDA46BB3E43C06C4" box="[426,577,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">E. humistrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E8804D45FF890169EE786BB3E57A06C4" box="[630,775,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="thymifolia">
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FF890169EE786BB3E57A06C4" box="[630,775,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">E. thymifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and in the past it was in some cases a misapplied name (for example to 
<taxonomicName id="E8804D45FF890169ED046857E7090518" box="[266,372,519,544]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nutans">
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FF890169ED046857E7090518" box="[266,372,519,544]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">E. nutans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; see 
<bibRefCitation id="4B114B37FF890169EDA26856E4D80519" author="Steinmann, V. W. &amp; Morawetz, J. J. &amp; Berry, P. E. &amp; Peirson, J. A. &amp; Yang, Y." box="[428,677,518,545]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="251 - 293" refId="ref34413" refString="Steinmann, V. W., Morawetz, J. J., Berry, P. E., Peirson, J. A. &amp; Yang, Y. (2016) Euphorbia Linnaeus sect. Anisophyllum Roeper. In: Rabeler, R. K. &amp; Hartman, R. L. (Eds.) Flora of North America 12. Oxford University Press, New York, Oxford, pp. 251 - 293." type="book chapter" year="2016">
Steinmann 
<emphasis id="1DF4EAD4FF890169EE246857E41F0518" box="[554,610,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
). It is noteworthy that many Italian authors (see 
